	<h1>Arenas</h1>
	<div class="description">
	The <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arena</a> is the place of choice for warrior players, where there is a chance to fight for glory and prestige. <p />
  There are several <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arenas</a> along in the <a href='/en/Universe/Default.aspx'>Universe</a>, whereas the more to the center of <a href='/en/Universe/Default.aspx'>Universe</a> the greater is the reward for victory. <p />
  When a player find an empty <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arena</a> he becomes automatically the champion of that <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arena</a>, otherwise he may challenge
  the current champion, and the <a href='/en/Universe/Fleet.aspx'>Fleet</a> of the battle will be a <a href='/en/Universe/Fleet.aspx'>Fleet</a> that is not chosen by any of the players, but will be a <a href='/en/Universe/Fleet.aspx'>Fleet</a> equal
  for both players made available by the <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arena</a> just for one battle. In case of victory the champion is uncrowned and
  a new champion is crowned for that <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arena</a>. <p />
  But the biggest incentive is the possibility of winning <a href='/en/Commerce/Orions.aspx'>Orions</a>. The challenger has to pay <a href='/en/Commerce/Orions.aspx'>Orions</a> to challenge the champion, if
  the champion wins the battle, he also wins part of the <a href='/en/Commerce/Orions.aspx'>Orions</a> paid by the challenger. The more <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arena</a> battles a player win more points 
  he wins for the profession of <a href='/en/GladiatorQuests.aspx'>Gladiator</a>.
  The only question is - <i>How many <a href='/en/Universe/Arenas.aspx'>Arenas</a> can you handle as champion?</i>
	</div>
	
